Majozi tabled two energetic back-to-back performances over the weekend at the newly opened Yoons @ Barnyard. The singer’s spirited performance took him into the crowd and even onto their tables, much to their delight. He even shared his microphone with some unsuspecting crowd members. ALSO READ: Woman with dead foetus left unattended in Rob Ferreira Hospital’s casualty Local talent Tessi Nandi also briefly graced the stage. Adding a little twist to his Saturday performance, he brought Nandi back onto the stage to help him out with a song as well. As the owner of the venue, Unice-Ann Badenhorst, said, “We love to bring people, food and laughter together.” It is safe to say that the love of these combined things came together in perfect harmony with these Friday and Saturday shows. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram